  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The King Dethrones Queen Vashti'
      title: The King Dethrones Queen Vashti
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the days of Ahasuerus (this was the Ahasuerus
        who reigned over one hundred and twenty-seven provinces, from India to Ethiopia), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'in those days when King Ahasuerus sat on the throne of his kingdom,
        which was in Shushan the citadel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "that in the third year of his reign he made a feast for all his officials
        and servants\u2014the powers of Persia and Media, the nobles, and the princes
        of the provinces being before him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: when he showed the riches of his glorious kingdom and the splendor
        of his excellent majesty for many days, one hundred and eighty days in  all.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when these days were completed, the king made a feast lasting
        seven days for all the people who were present in Shushan the citadel, from
        great to small, in the court of the garden of the king\u2019s palace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There  were white and blue linen curtains fastened with cords of
        fine linen and purple on silver rods and marble pillars; and  the  couches
        were of gold and silver on a mosaic pavement of alabaster, turquoise, and
        white and black marble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they served drinks in golden vessels, each vessel being different
        from the other, with royal wine in abundance, according to the generosity
        of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "In accordance with the law, the drinking was not compulsory; for
        so the king had ordered all the officers of his household, that they should
        do according to each man\u2019s pleasure."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Queen Vashti also made a feast for the women in the royal palace which
        belonged to King Ahasuerus.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine,
        he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, Abagtha, Zethar, and Carcas,
        seven eunuchs who served in the presence of King Ahasuerus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'to bring Queen Vashti before the king, wearing her royal crown, in
        order to show her beauty to the people and the officials, for she was beautiful
        to behold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Queen Vashti refused to come at the king\u2019s command brought
        by his eunuchs; therefore the king was furious, and his anger burned within
        him."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the king said to the wise men who understood the times (for
        this was the king\u2019s manner toward all who knew law and justice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "those closest to him being Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish,
        Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media, who had
        access to the king\u2019s presence, and who ranked highest in the kingdom): "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhat shall  we do to Queen Vashti, according to law, because
        she did not obey the command of King Ahasuerus brought  to  her by the eunuchs?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Memucan answered before the king and the princes: \u201CQueen
        Vashti has not only wronged the king, but also all the princes, and all the
        people who are in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For the queen\u2019s behavior will become known to all women, so
        that they will despise their husbands in their eyes, when they report, \u2018King
        Ahasuerus commanded Queen Vashti to be brought in before him, but she did
        not come.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "This very day the noble ladies of Persia and Media will say to all
        the king\u2019s officials that they have heard of the behavior of the queen.
        Thus there  will  be excessive contempt and wrath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If it pleases the king, let a royal decree go out from him, and let
        it be recorded in the laws of the Persians and the Medes, so that it will
        not be altered, that Vashti shall come no more before King Ahasuerus; and
        let the king give her royal position to another who is better than she. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When the king\u2019s decree which he will make is proclaimed throughout
        all his empire (for it is great), all wives will honor their husbands, both
        great and small.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the reply pleased the king and the princes, and the king did
        according to the word of Memucan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he sent letters to all the king\u2019s provinces, to each province
        in its own script, and to every people in their own language, that each man
        should be master in his own house, and speak in the language of his own people."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Becomes Queen'
      title: Esther Becomes Queen
      number: 1
      content: 'After these things, when the wrath of King Ahasuerus subsided, he
        remembered Vashti, what she had done, and what had been decreed against her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the king\u2019s servants who attended him said: \u201CLet beautiful
        young virgins be sought for the king; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and let the king appoint officers in all the provinces of his kingdom,
        that they may gather all the beautiful young virgins to Shushan the citadel,
        into the women\u2019s quarters, under the custody of Hegai the king\u2019s
        eunuch, custodian of the women. And let beauty preparations be given them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then let the young woman who pleases the king be queen instead of
        Vashti.\u201DThis thing pleased the king, and he did so."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In Shushan the citadel there was a certain Jew whose name was Mordecai
        the son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish, a Benjamite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Kish had been carried away from Jerusalem with the captives who had
        been captured with Jeconiah king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of
        Babylon had carried away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Mordecai had brought up Hadassah, that is, Esther, his uncle\u2019s
        daughter, for she had neither father nor mother. The young woman was lovely
        and beautiful. When her father and mother died, Mordecai took her as his
        own daughter."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So it was, when the king\u2019s command and decree were heard, and
        when many young women were gathered at Shushan the citadel, under the custody
        of Hegai, that Esther also was taken to the king\u2019s palace, into the
        care of Hegai the custodian of the women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now the young woman pleased him, and she obtained his favor; so he
        readily gave beauty preparations to her, besides her allowance. Then seven
        choice maidservants were provided for her from the king\u2019s palace, and
        he moved her and her maidservants to the best place in the house of the women."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Esther had not revealed her people or family, for Mordecai had charged
        her not to reveal it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And every day Mordecai paced in front of the court of the women\u2019s
        quarters, to learn of Esther\u2019s welfare and what was happening to her."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Each young woman\u2019s turn came to go in to King Ahasuerus after
        she had completed twelve months\u2019 preparation, according to the regulations
        for the women, for thus were the days of their preparation apportioned: six
        months with oil of myrrh, and six months with perfumes and preparations for
        beautifying women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus prepared, each young woman went to the king, and she was given
        whatever she desired to take with her from the women\u2019s quarters to the
        king\u2019s palace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "In the evening she went, and in the morning she returned to the second
        house of the women, to the custody of Shaashgaz, the king\u2019s eunuch who
        kept the concubines. She would not go in to the king again unless the king
        delighted in her and called for her by name."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now when the turn came for Esther the daughter of Abihail the uncle
        of Mordecai, who had taken her as his daughter, to go in to the king, she
        requested nothing but what Hegai the king\u2019s eunuch, the custodian of
        the women, advised. And Esther obtained favor in the sight of all who saw
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Esther was taken to King Ahasuerus, into his royal palace, in
        the tenth month, which is the month of Tebeth, in the seventh year of his
        reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The king loved Esther more than all the other women, and she obtained
        grace and favor in his sight more than all the virgins; so he set the royal
        crown upon her head and made her queen instead of Vashti. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Mordecai Discovers a Plot'
      title: Mordecai Discovers a Plot
      number: 18
      content: Then the king made a great feast, the Feast of Esther, for all his
        officials and servants; and he proclaimed a holiday in the provinces and
        gave gifts according to the generosity of a king.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When virgins were gathered together a second time, Mordecai sat within
        the king\u2019s gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Now Esther had not revealed her family and her people, just as Mordecai
        had charged her, for Esther obeyed the command of Mordecai as when she was
        brought up by him.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "In those days, while Mordecai sat within the king\u2019s gate, two
        of the king\u2019s eunuchs, Bigthan and Teresh, doorkeepers, became furious
        and sought to lay hands on King Ahasuerus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So the matter became known to Mordecai, who told Queen Esther, and
        Esther informed the king in Mordecai\u2019s name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And when an inquiry was made into the matter, it was confirmed, and
        both were hanged on a gallows; and it was written in the book of the chronicles
        in the presence of the king.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Haman\u2019s Conspiracy Against the Jews"
      title: "Haman\u2019s Conspiracy Against the Jews"
      number: 1
      content: 'After these things King Ahasuerus promoted Haman, the son of Hammedatha
        the Agagite, and advanced him and set his seat above all the princes who
        were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And all the king\u2019s servants who were  within the king\u2019s
        gate bowed and paid homage to Haman, for so the king had commanded concerning
        him. But Mordecai would not bow or pay homage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king\u2019s servants who were within the king\u2019s gate
        said to Mordecai, \u201CWhy do you transgress the king\u2019s command?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now it happened, when they spoke to him daily and he would not listen
        to them, that they told it to Haman, to see whether Mordecai\u2019s words
        would stand; for Mordecai had told them that he was a Jew. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Haman saw that Mordecai did not bow or pay him homage, Haman
        was filled with wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he disdained to lay hands on Mordecai alone, for they had told
        him of the people of Mordecai. Instead, Haman sought to destroy all the Jews
        who were throughout the whole kingdom of Ahasuerus\u2014the people of Mordecai."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In the first month, which is the month of Nisan, in the twelfth year
        of King Ahasuerus, they cast Pur (that is, the lot), before Haman to determine
        the day and the month, until it  fell  on  the twelfth month, which is the
        month of Adar.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Haman said to King Ahasuerus, \u201CThere is a certain people
        scattered and dispersed among the people in all the provinces of your kingdom;
        their laws are different from all other people\u2019s, and they do not keep
        the king\u2019s laws. Therefore it is not fitting for the king to let them
        remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If it pleases the king, let a  decree be written that they be destroyed,
        and I will pay ten thousand talents of silver into the hands of those who
        do the work, to bring it into the king\u2019s treasuries.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the king took his signet ring from his hand and gave it to Haman,
        the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the enemy of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the king said to Haman, \u201CThe money and the people are given
        to you, to do with them as seems good to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the king\u2019s scribes were called on the thirteenth day of
        the first month, and a  decree was written according to all that Haman commanded\u2014to
        the king\u2019s satraps, to the governors who were over each province, to
        the officials of all people, to every province according to its script, and
        to every people in their language. In the name of King Ahasuerus it was written,
        and sealed with the king\u2019s signet ring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the letters were sent by couriers into all the king\u2019s provinces,
        to destroy, to kill, and to annihilate all the Jews, both young and old,
        little children and women, in one day, on the thirteenth day of the twelfth
        month, which is the month of Adar, and to plunder their possessions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'A copy of the document was to be issued as law in every province,
        being published for all people, that they should be ready for that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The couriers went out, hastened by the king\u2019s command; and the
        decree was proclaimed in Shushan the citadel. So the king and Haman sat down
        to drink, but the city of Shushan was perplexed."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Agrees to Help the Jews'
      title: Esther Agrees to Help the Jews
      number: 1
      content: 'When Mordecai learned all that had happened, he tore his clothes
        and put on sackcloth and ashes, and went out into the midst of the city.
        He cried out with a loud and bitter cry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He went as far as the front of the king\u2019s gate, for no one might
        enter the king\u2019s gate clothed with sackcloth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And in every province where the king\u2019s command and decree arrived,
        there  was great mourning among the Jews, with fasting, weeping, and wailing;
        and many lay in sackcloth and ashes."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Esther\u2019s maids and eunuchs came and told her, and the queen
        was deeply distressed. Then she sent garments to clothe Mordecai and take
        his sackcloth away from him, but he would not accept them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Esther called Hathach, one of the king\u2019s eunuchs whom he
        had appointed to attend her, and she gave him a command concerning Mordecai,
        to learn what and why this was.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Hathach went out to Mordecai in the city square that was in front
        of the king\u2019s gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Mordecai told him all that had happened to him, and the sum of
        money that Haman had promised to pay into the king\u2019s treasuries to destroy
        the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He also gave him a copy of the written decree for their destruction,
        which was given at Shushan, that he might show it to Esther and explain it
        to her, and that he might command her to go in to the king to make supplication
        to him and plead before him for her people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So Hathach returned and told Esther the words of Mordecai.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Esther spoke to Hathach, and gave him a command for Mordecai: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAll the king\u2019s servants and the people of the king\u2019s
        provinces know that any man or woman who goes into the inner court to the
        king, who has not been called, he  has but one law: put all to death, except
        the one to whom the king holds out the golden scepter, that he may live.
        Yet I myself have not been called to go in to the king these thirty days.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So they told Mordecai Esther\u2019s words."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Mordecai told them to answer Esther: \u201CDo not think in your
        heart that you will escape in the king\u2019s palace any more than all the
        other Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For if you remain completely silent at this time, relief and deliverance
        will arise for the Jews from another place, but you and your father\u2019s
        house will perish. Yet who knows whether you have come to the kingdom for
        such a time as this?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Esther told them to reply to Mordecai: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo, gather all the Jews who are present in Shushan, and fast
        for me; neither eat nor drink for three days, night or day. My maids and
        I will fast likewise. And so I will go to the king, which is against the
        law; and if I perish, I perish!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So Mordecai went his way and did according to all that Esther commanded
        him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Esther\u2019s Banquet"
      title: "Esther\u2019s Banquet"
      number: 1
      content: "Now it happened on the third day that Esther put on her royal robes
        and stood in the inner court of the king\u2019s palace, across from the king\u2019s
        house, while the king sat on his royal throne in the royal house, facing
        the entrance of the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So it was, when the king saw Queen Esther standing in the court, that 
        she found favor in his sight, and the king held out to Esther the golden
        scepter that was in his hand. Then Esther went near and touched the top of
        the scepter.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said to her, \u201CWhat do you wish, Queen Esther? What
        is your request? It shall be given to you\u2014up to half the kingdom!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Esther answered, \u201CIf it pleases the king, let the king and
        Haman come today to the banquet that I have prepared for him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CBring Haman quickly, that he may do as
        Esther has said.\u201D So the king and Haman went to the banquet that Esther
        had prepared."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "At the banquet of wine the king said to Esther, \u201CWhat is your
        petition? It shall be granted you. What is your request, up to half the kingdom?
        It shall be done!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Esther answered and said, \u201CMy petition and request is 
        this:  "
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Haman\u2019s Plot Against Mordecai"
      title: "Haman\u2019s Plot Against Mordecai"
      number: 8
      content: "If I have found favor in the sight of the king, and if it pleases
        the king to grant my petition and fulfill my request, then let the king and
        Haman come to the banquet which I will prepare for them, and tomorrow I will
        do as the king has said.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Haman went out that day joyful and with a glad heart; but when
        Haman saw Mordecai in the king\u2019s gate, and that he did not stand or
        tremble before him, he was filled with indignation against Mordecai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Nevertheless Haman restrained himself and went home, and he sent
        and called for his friends and his wife Zeresh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then Haman told them of his great riches, the multitude of his children,
        everything in which the king had promoted him, and how he had advanced him
        above the officials and servants of the king.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Moreover Haman said, \u201CBesides, Queen Esther invited no one but
        me to come in with the king to the banquet that she prepared; and tomorrow
        I am again invited by her, along with the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet all this avails me nothing, so long as I see Mordecai the Jew
        sitting at the king\u2019s gate.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then his wife Zeresh and all his friends said to him, \u201CLet a
        gallows be made, fifty cubits high, and in the morning suggest to the king
        that Mordecai be hanged on it; then go merrily with the king to the banquet.\u201DAnd
        the thing pleased Haman; so he had the gallows made."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The King Honors Mordecai'
      title: The King Honors Mordecai
      number: 1
      content: 'That night the king could not sleep. So one was commanded to bring
        the book of the records of the chronicles; and they were read before the
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was found written that Mordecai had told of Bigthana and Teresh,
        two of the king\u2019s eunuchs, the doorkeepers who had sought to lay hands
        on King Ahasuerus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CWhat honor or dignity has been bestowed
        on Mordecai for this?\u201DAnd the king\u2019s servants who attended him
        said, \u201CNothing has been done for him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the king said, \u201CWho is in the court?\u201D Now Haman had
        just entered the outer court of the king\u2019s palace to suggest that the
        king hang Mordecai on the gallows that he had prepared for him."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CHaman is there, standing
        in the court.\u201DAnd the king said, \u201CLet him come in.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Haman came in, and the king asked him, \u201CWhat shall be done
        for the man whom the king delights to honor?\u201DNow Haman thought in his
        heart, \u201CWhom would the king delight to honor more than me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Haman answered the king, \u201CFor the man whom the king delights
        to honor, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'let a royal robe be brought which the king has worn, and a horse
        on which the king has ridden, which has a royal crest placed on its head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then let this robe and horse be delivered to the hand of one of the
        king\u2019s most noble princes, that he may array the man whom the king delights
        to honor. Then parade him on horseback through the city square, and proclaim
        before him: \u2018Thus shall it be done to the man whom the king delights
        to honor!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king said to Haman, \u201CHurry, take the robe and the horse,
        as you have suggested, and do so for Mordecai the Jew who sits within the
        king\u2019s gate! Leave nothing undone of all that you have spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Haman took the robe and the horse, arrayed Mordecai and led him
        on horseback through the city square, and proclaimed before him, \u201CThus
        shall it be done to the man whom the king delights to honor!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Afterward Mordecai went back to the king\u2019s gate. But Haman hurried
        to his house, mourning and with his head covered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Haman told his wife Zeresh and all his friends everything that
        had happened to him, his wise men and his wife Zeresh said to him, \u201CIf
        Mordecai, before whom you have begun to fall, is of Jewish descent, you will
        not prevail against him but will surely fall before him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "While they were still talking with him, the king\u2019s eunuchs came,
        and hastened to bring Haman to the banquet which Esther had prepared."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Haman Hanged Instead of Mordecai'
      title: Haman Hanged Instead of Mordecai
      number: 1
      content: 'So the king and Haman went to dine with Queen Esther. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And on the second day, at the banquet of wine, the king again said
        to Esther, \u201CWhat is your petition, Queen Esther? It shall be granted
        you. And what is your request, up to half the kingdom? It shall be done!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Queen Esther answered and said, \u201CIf I have found favor
        in your sight, O king, and if it pleases the king, let my life be given me
        at my petition, and my people at my request. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For we have been sold, my people and I, to be destroyed, to be killed,
        and to be annihilated. Had we been sold as male and female slaves, I would
        have held my tongue, although the enemy could never compensate for the king\u2019s
        loss.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So King Ahasuerus answered and said to Queen Esther, \u201CWho is
        he, and where is he, who would dare presume in his heart to do such a thing?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Esther said, \u201CThe adversary and enemy is this wicked Haman!\u201DSo
        Haman was terrified before the king and queen."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the king arose in his wrath from the banquet of wine and  went
        into the palace garden; but Haman stood before Queen Esther, pleading for
        his life, for he saw that evil was determined against him by the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When the king returned from the palace garden to the place of the
        banquet of wine, Haman had fallen across the couch where Esther was. Then
        the king said, \u201CWill he also assault the queen while I am in the house?\u201DAs
        the word left the king\u2019s mouth, they covered Haman\u2019s face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now Harbonah, one of the eunuchs, said to the king, \u201CLook! The
        gallows, fifty cubits high, which Haman made for Mordecai, who spoke good
        on the king\u2019s behalf, is standing at the house of Haman.\u201DThen the
        king said, \u201CHang him on it!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they hanged Haman on the gallows that he had prepared for Mordecai.
        Then the king\u2019s wrath subsided."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Saves the Jews'
      title: Esther Saves the Jews
      number: 1
      content: 'On that day King Ahasuerus gave Queen Esther the house of Haman,
        the enemy of the Jews. And Mordecai came before the king, for Esther had
        told how he was  related to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So the king took off his signet ring, which he had taken from Haman,
        and gave it to Mordecai; and Esther appointed Mordecai over the house of
        Haman.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Esther spoke again to the king, fell down at his feet, and implored
        him with tears to counteract the evil of Haman the Agagite, and the scheme
        which he had devised against the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king held out the golden scepter toward Esther. So Esther
        arose and stood before the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said, \u201CIf it pleases the king, and if I have found favor
        in his sight and the thing seems right to the king and I am pleasing in his
        eyes, let it be written to revoke the letters devised by Haman, the son of
        Hammedatha the Agagite, which he wrote to annihilate the Jews who are in
        all the king\u2019s provinces. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For how can I endure to see the evil that will come to my people?
        Or how can I endure to see the destruction of my countrymen?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then King Ahasuerus said to Queen Esther and Mordecai the Jew, \u201CIndeed,
        I have given Esther the house of Haman, and they have hanged him on the gallows
        because he tried  to lay his hand on the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You yourselves write a  decree concerning the Jews, as you please,
        in the king\u2019s name, and seal it with the king\u2019s signet ring; for
        whatever is written in the king\u2019s name and sealed with the king\u2019s
        signet ring no one can revoke.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So the king\u2019s scribes were called at that time, in the third
        month, which is the month of Sivan, on the twenty-third day; and it was written,
        according to all that Mordecai commanded, to the Jews, the satraps, the governors,
        and the princes of the provinces from India to Ethiopia, one hundred and
        twenty-seven provinces in  all, to every province in its own script, to every
        people in their own language, and to the Jews in their own script and language. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he wrote in the name of King Ahasuerus, sealed it with the king\u2019s
        signet ring, and sent letters by couriers on horseback, riding on royal horses
        bred from swift steeds."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "By these letters the king permitted the Jews who were in every city
        to gather together and protect their lives\u2014to destroy, kill, and annihilate
        all the forces of any people or province that would assault them, both little
        children and women, and to plunder their possessions, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'on one day in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus, on the thirteenth
        day of the twelfth month, which is the month of Adar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A copy of the document was to be issued as a decree in every province
        and published for all people, so that the Jews would be ready on that day
        to avenge themselves on their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The couriers who rode on royal horses went out, hastened and pressed
        on by the king\u2019s command. And the decree was issued in Shushan the citadel."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal apparel
        of blue and white, with a great crown of gold and a garment of fine linen
        and purple; and the city of Shushan rejoiced and was glad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Jews had light and gladness, joy and honor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And in every province and city, wherever the king\u2019s command
        and decree came, the Jews had joy and gladness, a feast and a holiday. Then
        many of the people of the land became Jews, because fear of the Jews fell
        upon them."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Jews Destroy Their Tormentors'
      title: The Jews Destroy Their Tormentors
      number: 1
      content: "Now in the twelfth month, that is, the month of Adar, on the thirteenth
        day, the  time came for the king\u2019s command and his decree to be executed.
        On the day that the enemies of the Jews had hoped to overpower them, the
        opposite occurred, in that the Jews themselves overpowered those who hated
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Jews gathered together in their cities throughout all the provinces
        of King Ahasuerus to lay hands on those who sought their harm. And no one
        could withstand them, because fear of them fell upon all people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And all the officials of the provinces, the satraps, the governors,
        and all those doing the king\u2019s work, helped the Jews, because the fear
        of Mordecai fell upon them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For Mordecai was great in the king\u2019s palace, and his fame spread
        throughout all the provinces; for this man Mordecai became increasingly prominent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Thus the Jews defeated all their enemies with the stroke of the sword,
        with slaughter and destruction, and did what they pleased with those who
        hated them.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And in Shushan the citadel the Jews killed and destroyed five hundred
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also Parshandatha, Dalphon, Aspatha, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Poratha, Adalia, Aridatha, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Parmashta, Arisai, Aridai, and Vajezatha\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "the ten sons of Haman the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews\u2014they
        killed; but they did not lay a hand on the plunder."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On that day the number of those who were killed in Shushan the citadel
        was brought to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the king said to Queen Esther, \u201CThe Jews have killed and
        destroyed five hundred men in Shushan the citadel, and the ten sons of Haman.
        What have they done in the rest of the king\u2019s provinces? Now what is
        your petition? It shall be granted to you. Or what is your further request?
        It shall be done.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Esther said, \u201CIf it pleases the king, let it be granted
        to the Jews who are in Shushan to do again tomorrow according to today\u2019s
        decree, and let Haman\u2019s ten sons be hanged on the gallows.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the king commanded this to be done; the decree was issued in Shushan,
        and they hanged Haman\u2019s ten sons."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And the Jews who were in Shushan gathered together again on the fourteenth
        day of the month of Adar and killed three hundred men at Shushan; but they
        did not lay a hand on the plunder.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The remainder of the Jews in the king\u2019s provinces gathered together
        and protected their lives, had rest from their enemies, and killed seventy-five
        thousand of their enemies; but they did not lay a hand on the plunder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Feast of Purim'
      title: The Feast of Purim
      number: 17
      content: This  was on the thirteenth day of the month of Adar. And on the fourteenth
        of the  month they rested and made it a day of feasting and gladness.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the Jews who were at Shushan assembled together on the thirteenth
        day, as well as on the fourteenth; and on the fifteenth of the  month they
        rested, and made it a day of feasting and gladness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Therefore the Jews of the villages who dwelt in the unwalled towns
        celebrated the fourteenth day of the month of Adar with gladness and feasting,
        as a holiday, and for sending presents to one another.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Mordecai wrote these things and sent letters to all the Jews,
        near and far, who were in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'to establish among them that they should celebrate yearly the fourteenth
        and fifteenth days of the month of Adar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'as the days on which the Jews had rest from their enemies, as the
        month which was turned from sorrow to joy for them, and from mourning to
        a holiday; that they should make them days of feasting and joy, of sending
        presents to one another and gifts to the poor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the Jews accepted the custom which they had begun, as Mordecai
        had written to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'because Haman, the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the enemy of all
        the Jews, had plotted against the Jews to annihilate them, and had cast Pur
        (that is, the lot), to consume them and destroy them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: but when Esther came before the king, he commanded by letter that
        this wicked plot which Haman had devised against the Jews should return on
        his own head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So they called these days Purim, after the name Pur. Therefore, because
        of all the words of this letter, what they had seen concerning this matter,
        and what had happened to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the Jews established and imposed it upon themselves and their descendants
        and all who would join them, that without fail they should celebrate these
        two days every year, according to the written instructions and according
        to the prescribed time, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: that these days should  be remembered and kept throughout every generation,
        every family, every province, and every city, that these days of Purim should
        not fail to  be  observed among the Jews, and that the memory of them should
        not perish among their descendants.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Queen Esther, the daughter of Abihail, with Mordecai the Jew,
        wrote with full authority to confirm this second letter about Purim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Mordecai sent letters to all the Jews, to the one hundred and
        twenty-seven provinces of the kingdom of Ahasuerus, with words of peace and
        truth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'to confirm these days of Purim at their appointed time, as Mordecai
        the Jew and Queen Esther had prescribed for them, and as they had decreed
        for themselves and their descendants concerning matters of their fasting
        and lamenting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: So the decree of Esther confirmed these matters of Purim, and it was
        written in the book.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Mordecai\u2019s Advancement"
      title: "Mordecai\u2019s Advancement"
      number: 1
      content: 'And King Ahasuerus imposed tribute on the land and on  the islands
        of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now all the acts of his power and his might, and the account of the
        greatness of Mordecai, to which the king advanced him, are they not written
        in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Media and Persia? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For Mordecai the Jew was  second to King Ahasuerus, and was great
        among the Jews and well received by the multitude of his brethren, seeking
        the good of his people and speaking peace to all his countrymen.
      comments: []
